<title>UK: UK firms oppose joining first wave of EMU - paper.</title>
<headline>UK firms oppose joining first wave of EMU - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Most small and medium-sized British companies are opposed to Britain joining a single European currency when it is due to come into existence in 1999, the Financial Times reported on Monday.</p>
<p>The newspaper said an analysis of interviews with 81 executives showed just 29 percent believed Britain should join at the planned start of the project. Twenty percent said Britain should never join.</p>
<p>However, 58 percent said European Monetary Union (EMU) would be good in principle for their firms. Only 14 percent said it would be bad.</p>
